^XMB(3.9,145971,2,3,0)=" "
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,4,0)="The following active entries in your DRUG file (#50) have been unmatched from"
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,5,0)="the National Drug File (NDF).  The VA Product name and CMOP ID corresponding"
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,6,0)="to the unmatched local drug file name are listed on the indented line beneath"
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,7,0)="each entry.  An Inactivation Date may be listed for entries when this reason "
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,8,0)="applies.  Until you rematch these entries to NDF, they will not transmit to"
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,9,0)="CMOP and drug-drug interaction checks will not check for these products.  It"
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,10,0)="is critical that you rematch these products immediately.  You may also need"
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,11,0)="to match a new orderable item.  Any possible dosages and local possible "
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,12,0)="dosages for these unmatched products have been deleted. Therefore, the"
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,13,0)="dosages for each unmatched product should be reviewed after the rematch or"
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,14,0)="recreated if the product can not be rematched to a VA Product through the NDF "
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,15,0)="matching process.  "
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,16,0)=" "
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,17,0)=""
