^XMB(3.9,145971,2,29,0)="The following investigational entries in your DRUG file (#50) have been "
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,30,0)="unmatched from the National Drug File (NDF).  The VA Product name and CMOP ID"
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,31,0)="corresponding to the unmatched local drug file name are listed on the"
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,32,0)="indented line beneath each entry.  An Inactivation Date may be listed for"
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,33,0)="entries when this reason applies.  Until you rematch these entries to NDF,"
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,34,0)="they will not transmit to CMOP and drug-drug interaction checks will not"
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,35,0)="check for these products.  It is critical that you rematch these products"
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,36,0)="immediately.  You may also need to match a new orderable item.  Any possible"
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,37,0)="dosages and local possible dosages for these unmatched products have been"
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,38,0)="deleted. Therefore, the dosages for each unmatched product should be reviewed"
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,39,0)="after the rematch or recreated if the product can not be rematched to a VA"
^XMB(3.9,145971,2,40,0)="Product through the NDF matching process.  "
